  "text": "Reward models are used to specify measures of system behaviour [CITATION_1] . A reward model has two different reward components: one is concerned with 'rate rewards', that is, the rate at which reward accumulates while the process is in a specified set of markings during an interval of time; and the other is concerned with 'impulse rewards', based on the count of the number of times a transition fires during an interval of time.",
